divs: Sighting DetailsWhile laying in bed at night I heard a low humming almost similiar to a oscilatting motor aproach from the south. It took almost 5 minutes for it to approach. Once over my house the noise sounded very low altitude. I was to tired to look outside, but the noise sent chills up my spine. The noise steadily dissipated over the next five minutes to the north, to what sounded like a perfect linear pathway. If anyone else reports this same incident I would love to be put in contact with them so I know that I am not going crazy!
